parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: engine knocking or making loud noises

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: loud noises or rattling sounds from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Catalytic converter failure can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: loud noises or rattling sounds from the exhaust

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and power loss can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: vehicle slowing down or losing speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: or fails to accelerate; the transmission warning light illuminates; the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall, lose power, or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start; the timing chain warning light illuminates; the engine makes abnormal noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can cause engine damage, leading to premature wear and potentially catastrophic engine failure.
symptoms: The engine consumes excessive oil; the oil warning light illuminates; the engine makes abnormal noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Stability Control (ESC) and StabiliTrak Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC and StabiliTrak systems can cause the vehicle to lose traction, stability, or control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The ESC and StabiliTrak warning lights illuminate; the vehicle loses traction
or control; the vehicle makes abnormal noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning lights and gauges to malfunction, leading to a loss of critical information for the driver, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Warning lights and gauges flashing or not functioning
and strange noises from the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster/heater system can cause the windshield to fog up, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and strange noises from the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery and charging system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: and strange noises from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents and potentially causing damage to the engine.
symptoms: and strange noises from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: and strange noises from the dashboard.
